# Privacy Policy

**App:** KiwiScribe – NZ Books
**Last updated:** 11 July 2026

KiwiScribe is a catalogue of New Zealand books. Your privacy matters, and the app
is built to need as little of your information as possible.

## The short version

- **We do not collect any personal information.**
- **We do not track you**, and there are no advertising or analytics identifiers.
- **There is no account or login.**
- Anything you save in the app (such as your reading list) stays **on your device**.

## Information stored on your device

KiwiScribe stores your app data — such as books you add to your list, reading
status, and app settings — **locally on your device** only. This information is
not sent to us or to anyone else, and we cannot see it.

## Network connections

KiwiScribe connects to the internet only in two limited ways:

1. **Book cover images** are loaded from public book-data services (such as Google
   Books and Open Library) so covers can be shown.
2. **Bookshop links** — when you choose to find or buy a book, the app opens a New
   Zealand bookshop's website in an in-app browser.

When your device requests an image or opens a website, that third-party service
receives standard technical information (such as your device's IP address) needed
to serve the request. This is handled under **those services' own privacy
policies**, not by KiwiScribe, and we do not receive any of that information.

## Data we collect: none

We do not collect, store, share, or sell any personal data. There is no tracking,
profiling, or advertising.

## Children

KiwiScribe does not collect data from anyone, including children.

## Changes to this policy

If this policy changes, the updated version will be posted on this page with a new
"Last updated" date.

